{"info": {"author": "Davide Vitelaru", "author_email": "davide@vitelaru.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# OneService\n\nWrapper around Flask aimed at conveniently creating microservices.\n\nFeatures and limitations:\n- `Microservice` creates a server that can call a handler method when `/` is hit (HTTP method is configurable)\n- The handler method receives the request JSON data and must respond with a `(dict, int)` tuple containing\nthe response data and response status code\n\n## Usage\n```python\nfrom oneservice import Microservice\n\ndef return_doubled(json_data: dict) -> (dict, int):\n    return {\"result\": int(json_data[\"a\"]) * 2}, 200\n\nm = Microservice(handler=return_doubled)\nm.start()\n```\n\nYou may then hit the microservice and its health endpoint:\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:5000/health\ncurl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"a\": 2}' http://localhost:5000/\n```\n\nSee [/examples](examples) for more code usage samples.\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/davidevi/oneservice", "keywords": "microservice,micro,service,oneservice,one", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "oneservice", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/oneservice/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/oneservice/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://gitlab.com/davidevi/oneservice", "Repository": "https://gitlab.com/davidevi/oneservice"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/oneservice/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": ["flask (>=1.1.2,<2.0.0)"], "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "summary": "Wrapper around Flask aimed at conveniently creating microservices", "version": "1.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>OneService</h1>\n<p>Wrapper around Flask aimed at conveniently creating microservices.</p>\n<p>Features and limitations:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>Microservice</code> creates a server that can call a handler method when <code>/</code> is hit (HTTP method is configurable)</li>\n<li>The handler method receives the request JSON data and must respond with a <code>(dict, int)</code> tuple containing\nthe response data and response status code</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">oneservice</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Microservice</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">return_doubled</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">json_data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nb\">dict</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">dict</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nb\">int</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"s2\">\"result\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nb\">int</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">json_data</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s2\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"p\">])</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">},</span> <span class=\"mi\">200</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">m</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Microservice</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handler</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">return_doubled</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n<p>You may then hit the microservice and its health endpoint:</p>\n<pre>curl http://localhost:5000/health\ncurl -X POST -H <span class=\"s2\">\"Content-Type: application/json\"</span> --data <span class=\"s1\">'{\"a\": 2}'</span> http://localhost:5000/\n</pre>\n<p>See <a href=\"examples\" rel=\"nofollow\">/examples</a> for more code usage samples.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7044316, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "dacd2f2c0238a6aaf139745127a444b3", "sha256": "cf2692954b56ef1dcba99250c8e0b4b5452ea5256f07ce208737418d66acfe14"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "oneservice-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "dacd2f2c0238a6aaf139745127a444b3", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "size": 3305, "upload_time": "2020-04-17T18:44:00", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-17T18:44:00.410604Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/4b/f9/573e1a03ba5d46997cea2b63b9fb79cacca3a40a4cbcb8c8a02b0cba1efa/oneservice-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e20d7220113353f437cc6bda8884b3ed", "sha256": "29628701500e9007c4c57b515c37de837ba763cd504a5e9367bc8d79adfef07a"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "oneservice-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e20d7220113353f437cc6bda8884b3ed", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "size": 2992, "upload_time": "2020-04-17T18:44:02", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-17T18:44:02.368228Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e2/74/8a874789a4f31e8e2141603e915668d7cd9fad9a018d84af7c32835c0ec2/oneservice-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2777dbd1f5564a19f49822813c252459", "sha256": "9ac9fbb499fd823676bbea75455d1bb94830eb2abfa4f752ca5c1c9dc6aadb8e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "oneservice-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2777dbd1f5564a19f49822813c252459", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "size": 3311, "upload_time": "202